10.9.18  6:18 pm   You know what my favorite bob ross thing is? When he get's really frisky and makes one of those "big decisions" where the painting is almost done and he's like, 'you know what, this is your world, and maybe you want a tree to live right here' and he just grabs his two inch brush (dips it in odorless paint thinner and beats the devil out of it) and paints a giant damn tree front and center that covers half the canvass.... Sometimes, I wish I had the courage to do that in my music. 

     actually,
those paintings are not improvised. he is looking at a finished copy for reference. but, that is also my favorite part because you can see him speed up, and you can see him watch the clock. you can feel the panic and madness start to set in as we are at 3 minutes left and there are still huge empty spaces to fill
